<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880203-0169 </DOCNO><HL> Emhart to Raise Spending 13% </HL><SO> </SO><CO> EMH </CO><DATELINE> FARMINGTON, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Emhart Corp. said it plans to raise capital spending 13% for 1988, to about $106 million.    The industrial products and information services concern said it would allocate the largest share of total capital spending, about 43%, for automation, additional equipment and other improvements to reduce production costs. </TEXT></DOC>